What is OnPush Strategy in Angular?

OnPush is an Angular Change Detection strategy that tells Angular to check and update a component only when its input data changes, an event occurs inside the component, or manual change detection is triggered. It helps reduce unnecessary component re-rendering and improves application performance.

Why do we use OnPush Strategy in Angular?

OnPush strategy is used to optimize Angular application performance by minimizing unnecessary change detection cycles. It is especially useful in large applications where multiple components are rendered frequently.

For Example
import { Component, ChangeDetectionStrategy, Input } from'@angular/core';

@Component({
 selector: 'app-user',
 template: `<h2>{{ user }}</h2>`,
 changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush
})
exportclassUserComponent {
@Input() user!: string;
}

<app-user[user]="username"></app-user>

In this example, Angular updates the component only when the username input value changes instead of checking it continuously.



